"structures of the tracheo-broncheal tree, natural or artificial opening-part a. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the tracheo-broncheal tree via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0b.. . "
"structures of the tracheo-broncheal tree, natural or artificial opening-part a. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the tracheo-broncheal tree via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0b.. revision of nonautologous tissue substitute in trachea,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to revision of nonautologous tissue substitute in trachea,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0bw18kz. "

"structures of the tracheo-broncheal tree, natural or artificial opening-part a. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the tracheo-broncheal tree via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0b.. restriction of left main bronchus via natural or artificial opening intraluminal device,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to restriction of left main bronchus via natural or artificial opening intraluminal device,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0bv78dz. "structures of the tracheo-broncheal tree, open approach-part b. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the tracheo-broncheal tree with open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0b.. resection of left lower lobe bronchus,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to resection of left lower lobe bronchus,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0btb0zz. "

"

"structures of the tracheo-broncheal tree, percutaneous endoscopic approach-part b. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the tracheo-broncheal tree with percutaneous endoscopic approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0b.. release left lower lobe bronchus,  percutaneous endoscopic approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to release left lower lobe bronchus,  percutaneous endoscopic approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0bnb4zz. "

"structures of the lungs and pleura, natural or artificial opening-part a. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the lungs and pleura, natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0b.. revision of diaphragmatic pacemaker lead in diaphragm,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to revision of diaphragmatic pacemaker lead in diaphragm,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0bwt8mz.
